NAME
    echo - display a line of text

SYNOPSIS
    echo [OPTION]... [STRING]...

DESCRIPTION
    Echo the STRING(s) to standard output, separated by spaces and
    followed by a newline.

    Note: Many shells provide a built-in echo command. This man page
    describes the Winix standalone echo utility. Behavior may differ
    from the shell built-in.

OPTIONS
    -n  Do not output the trailing newline.

    -e  Enable interpretation of backslash escapes.

    -E  Disable interpretation of backslash escapes (default).

    --version
        Output version information and exit.

    --help
        Display help and exit.

ESCAPE SEQUENCES
    With -e, the following sequences are recognized:

    \\      Backslash
    \a      Alert (BEL)
    \b      Backspace
    \c      Suppress further output (including trailing newline)
    \e      Escape character
    \f      Form feed
    \n      Newline
    \r      Carriage return
    \t      Horizontal tab
    \v      Vertical tab
    \0NNN   Byte with octal value NNN (0 to 3 digits)
    \xHH    Byte with hexadecimal value HH

EXAMPLES
    echo Hello, World!
        Print a simple greeting.

    echo "Current dir: $(pwd)"
        Print current directory with command substitution.

    echo -n "Enter name: "
        Print without trailing newline (for prompts).

    echo -e "Line 1\nLine 2\nLine 3"
        Print three lines using escape sequences.

    echo -e "\t\tIndented text"
        Print text indented with two tabs.

    echo "" > file.txt
        Write a blank line to file.txt.

    echo "result: $((2 + 2))"
        Print result of arithmetic expansion.

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success.
    1   Error occurred.
